@node History "qboot - History"
      ---------------------------------------------------------------

      1.07    (21/09/2014)    === Bugs eliminated ===

        * Added 'Quit' wrapper to mask non-interpreted lines. It does
        work the same way as 'Skip'. Also, when PROMPT/S is requested
        then  backspelled  'EndCLI'  will be used instead of skipping
        over it. This replacement is an alias of 'Quit'.

        * Due to reworked logo handling code (in 'qdev') an animation 
        sub-task does not get negative priority no more.  This should
        ensure smooth animation during loading.

        * Fixed  certain line parser related bugs so quotation is now
        handled properly.

        * Fixed  nasty bugs in  'Execute'  replacement where typeless
        args were  messing up whole template. Also, the  script event
        handler  was freed from a  "feature" which allowed erreoneous
        script to pass.

        * Arg. translator  ("QUIET", "NIL:")  performance tweaks have
        been applied. 

        * There is  a new debug feature which allows to link consoles
        so instead of  having two consoles on different monitors they
        can  show up  on the same screen. To activate this mode stuff
        word "CURRENT" in ALTID/K .

        * Std  SIGBREAKF_CTRL_#? signals work now from both consoles.

        * Fails now peacefully under earlier OS releases (below V39).


      1.06    (10/03/2014)    === Bugs eliminated ===

        * Scripts that were to be called from current directory could
        not be opened, oops!

        * Text cursor is now  invisible  in progress bar mode so that
        no annoying jumps occur.


      1.05    (06/01/2014)    === Happy New Year! ===

        * New year means new build (linked against more optimized and
        debugged library). Small speed increase can be expected.

        * All raw  ESC codes have been turned into '*e' in the config
        file. Some  editors do not handle  non-displayable characters
        too well.

        * Command stepping option accepts now line range to slow down
        at the desired line(s). There is also new style holder due to
        that called SL=SLSTYLES/K .

        * From now on binary contains library information in the $VER
        string.

        * Added FAQ section to this guide.


      1.04    (06/11/2013)    === Add-ons release ===

        * Progress bar option was implemented so that booting on slow
        graphics hardware (scrolling involved) does not take ages.

        * Inner  workings concept changes  here and there. See source
        code for more.


      1.03    (03/11/2013)    === Bugs eliminated ===

        BUGS REPORTED BY: Stellan Pistoor

          * Logging to a file was done through  "buffer push" so last
          lines  did  not end  up  being  saved, not  until  file was
          closed.

          * Logfile  was splitted across main and background channels
          using distinct FHs which resulted in messy output.

        * Certain cosmetic changes have been made to  FDR handling to
        improve performance and functionality.

        * Local variable  $CON that was holding main channel location
        was replaced by device alias '[C]:'.

        * Timer assisted command stepping was implemented, so that it
        is possible to slow down script flow.

        * Base script can now be  unlocked after reaching EOF/prompt.
        This is active in new configuration file by default.


      1.02    (11/10/2013)    === Bugs eliminated ===

        BUGS REPORTED BY: Stellan Pistoor

          * Scripts that lacked 'Execute' initializer were handled by
          the  original command that  unfortunately  is incompatible.
          This bug was introduced in 1.01 -- Thanks for investigating
          man!

          * Strange Enforcer hits triggered by  Directory Opus 5  own
          device lister were FDR related. Subsystem is now patched.

        * Argh, 'qboot' turned out to be useless under  39.xxx due to
        broken shell in that OS release. Please use "****" instead of
        two naked asterisks at the command line.

        * Had  to look into  ROM  again to  figure  out how  to write
        'SetVBuf()' replacement which is unimplemented in  39.xxx and
        below. This  should  fix another  bug related  to script line
        handling.

        * Missing line number acknowledge was added. From now on line
        number is correct as per base script no matter 'qboot' pos. 


      1.01    (21/09/2013)    === Bugs eliminated ===

        BUGS REPORTED BY: Stellan Pistoor

          * Shell's  line buffer was too small causing premature line
          splits that caused weird problems  such as  comments  being
          treated like commands or wrong line numbering.

          * When L=LOGO/K in the config was commented then it did act
          like an image  thus unititialized  'datatypes.library'  was
          bringing up warning requester...

        * An  'Execute' command when called from a path ('C:' mostly)
        was not detected thus  'qboot'  replacement could not be used
        which was the cause of all sort of weirdness.

        * New option MK=MUTEKB/K was added so that console won't hear
        raw key presses and thus  will not block during booting. Some
        Amigans  do use tools that  grab key states  allowing them to
        change script flow - they will work now with 'qboot'.


      1.00    (17/03/2013)    === Initial release ===

        * It took me  17  days to write this program and another this
        period to debug and master it, but no changelog is available.

        * Currently height of  top-left corner logo is  limited to 60
        pixels. You  can change this  for yourself by altering screen
        structure(see examples in 'qdev').

        * One interesting problem that is still not resolved concerns
        'Skip' command and indentation. When you jump outside current
        conditional then indentation does not denest!

        * Secondary console does only ACTION_READ and ACTION_WRITE so
        programs  started in there  may not be  able to switch to raw
        mode. This will not be fixed I am afraid.

        * It is not a bug when you see command that spells backwards!
        These are private 'qboot' commands.

        * As to  size of the binary,  yes I know it weights too much,
        but currently I cannot help it...

      ---------------------------------------------------------------
@endnode



